<span id="freeTextContainer4185371347641224706"><b>3.5 🐎 🐎 🐎</b><br/>This is one I want to use the two level scoring method for. There&apos;s the writing and then the story. The first gets a 5 and the latter a 3. It&apos;s less is more storytelling that you must pay attention to because blink and you&apos;ve missed it. <br/>Trond a 67 year old man has made the decision to live a minimalist lifestyle in isolation in rural Norway. He&apos;s not told anyone where he is and has no phone. Back from a walk he is surprised to see his daughter has tracked him down and come to visit. A w</span>
  <span id="freeText4185371347641224706" style="display:none"><b>3.5 🐎 🐎 🐎</b><br />This is one I want to use the two level scoring method for. There's the writing and then the story. The first gets a 5 and the latter a 3. It's less is more storytelling that you must pay attention to because blink and you've missed it. <br />Trond a 67 year old man has made the decision to live a minimalist lifestyle in isolation in rural Norway. He's not told anyone where he is and has no phone. Back from a walk he is surprised to see his daughter has tracked him down and come to visit. A while later she asks him<br />"Would you rather I hadn't come?" <br />"I don't know" he replies.<br />That's how I feel about Trond. Did I like him and his story? I don't know. I'm usually a great fan of minimalism but in this case I wanted more and was left feeling, well, isolated. The thing is Trond could care less I'm sure.</span>
