<div id="review_3038544371" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3038544371" />
    <a title="Antoinette" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/5328952-antoinette"><img alt="Antoinette" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1503842818p2/5328952.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3038544371?book_show_action=true">Apr 18, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Antoinette" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Antoinette" href="/user/show/5328952-antoinette">Antoinette</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Kindle Edition " href="/book/show/20696580-out-stealing-horses">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/5328952-antoinette?shelf=favorites">favorites</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/5328952-antoinette?shelf=norwegian">norwegian</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3038544371" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer8514593463051386757">This is an extraordinary book! The writing was exceptional; the translation- seems flawless and the story- well the story just wrapped itself around my insides and stayed with me even when I wasn’t reading.<br/><br/>This book is about Trond, a 67 yr old man, who has gone off to live in a secluded cabin in the woods. No telephone, no television, just Trond and his dog Lyra.<br/><br/>“Time is important to me now, I tell myself. Not that it should pass quickly or slowly, but be only time, be something I live inside an</span>
  <span id="freeText8514593463051386757" style="display:none">This is an extraordinary book! The writing was exceptional; the translation- seems flawless and the story- well the story just wrapped itself around my insides and stayed with me even when I wasn’t reading.<br /><br />This book is about Trond, a 67 yr old man, who has gone off to live in a secluded cabin in the woods. No telephone, no television, just Trond and his dog Lyra.<br /><br />“Time is important to me now, I tell myself. Not that it should pass quickly or slowly, but be only time, be something I live inside and fill with physical things and activities that I can divide it up by, so that it grows distinct to me and does not vanish when I am not looking.”<br /><br />One day he meets his neighbour, a man he once knew from a day and time he has suppressed. That meeting brings back all the memories, which he now has to confront.It’s hard to confront a moment which has shaped you irrevocably for the rest of your life. <br /><br />“And when someone says the past is a foreign country,that they do things differently there, then I have probably felt that way for most of my life because I have been obliged to, but I am not sure anymore. If I just concentrate I can walk into memory’s store and find the right shelf with the right film and disappear into it and feel in my body that ride through the forest with my father.....”<br /><br />This book deeply affected me. It is an extraordinary book- but it has to be sipped like a fine wine and not rushed through.<br />Highly recommended!!</span>
  <a data-text-id="8514593463051386757" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


